data.body:
This PR removes the project files and templates for Windows 8.1 Store and Phone. With the release of Visual 2017,  it will no longer be possible to build Windows 8.1 Store and Phone apps with VS2017. Microsoft is no longer supporting Angle for Windows 8.1 apps. Microsoft will no longer support  Windows 8.1 apps in Cocos2d-x starting with v3.15. This PR depends on https://github.com/cocos2d/cocos2d-x-3rd-party-libs-bin/pull/270.

Developers who wish to use cocos2d-x for Windows 8.1 apps will have to use cocos2d-x v3.14.1 or earlier.

@minggo  Note: The cocos2d-x Jenkins build system will need to be updated to build the Windows 10 universal version of cocos2d-x and not the Windows 8.1 Universal. This PR will fail until Windows 8.1 Universal builds are removed from Jenkins.
